From: Sanket Bumb <sanket@yourowncrm.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 19:16:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: resource hours date ranges, per-day location, bulk-save
 (fixes race condition)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause of 'only second configuration saves':
- Previous saveHours() fired 7-14 parallel POST requests (one per day per
  config), each independently re-reading existing rows and upserting by
  (dayOfWeek, priority). Under concurrency, these requests raced —
  whichever committed LAST for a given (day, priority) won, so earlier
  configs' data was frequently lost or overwritten.

Fix — bulk replace endpoint:
- New PUT /api/resource-schedules?entityType=X&entityId=Y accepts the
  ENTIRE schedule as one request: { rows: [...] }
- Backend deletes all existing rows for the entity and re-inserts the
  full set in ONE transaction — no race condition possible
- Old single-row POST kept for backward compatibility

Resource Hours UI — new fields per requirements:
- Each config card now has Start Date (required) and End Date (optional,
  blank = 'Always Active', shown with a badge)
- Location moved from the config-card header to a PER-DAY dropdown in
  the days table, with 'All Locations' as a working option (null
  locationId on the row)
- Copy Monday now also copies the location selection
- Status column shows the assigned location per day when set
- Frontend validates Start Date is required and End Date >= Start Date
  before saving; backend also validates and throws BusinessException

Backend — ResourceScheduleController:
- applyRowFields() validates and sets effectiveFrom (required) and
  effectiveTo (optional, null = always active) per row
- locationId per row resolves to a Location entity or null ('All
  Locations') — previously this was only possible at config level
- toResponse() DTO now includes startDate/endDate alongside
  locationId/locationName/locationColor

Schedule grid — location color bands:
- Now filtered by the VIEWED date (state.currentDate), not hardcoded
  'today' — navigating dates shows that date's bands correctly
- Bands respect each row's effective date range (startDate/endDate)
  so expired or future-dated configs don't show on the wrong dates
- Same date-range filter applied to the dynamic hour-range calculation
